<h2>Namespacing</h2>
This namespacing method was posted on HN which I found very interesting.  
[HN discussion](http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=871777). This in a way is very similar to the way Google's Closure namespaces with the required() method.

<div  class="code-block console-wrap"><div class="code code-block">
<code>
 var namespace = function(ns) {
    var scope = window;
    var tokens = ns.split(".");
    for (var idx = 0, len = tokens.length; idx < len; idx++) {
      var token = tokens[idx];
      scope = scope[token] = scope[token] || {};
    }
  };

namespace('Zen.Ui.jump.too');
Zen.UI = 2;
log(Zen.UI);
log(typeof  Zen.Ui.jump.too);

</code>

</div>

